        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 3:58PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 358 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
San Acacio, or 26 miles southeast of San Luis Valley Airport, moving
southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
San Acacio, Chama, San Luis, Mesita, San Pablo, and Sanchez
Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM MDT for
southeastern Colorado.</instruction>
